The paper deals with the problem of constructing an optimal aggregation tree in wireless sensor networks (WSNs) with deadline constraints. This problem involves network optimization, distributed algorithms, and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes two distributed algorithms with different computation overheads, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper uses the Markov approximation framework, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
